The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (ND­LEA), Niger Command, has said it arrested 61 suspected drug traffickers in different parts of the state in 2020. The Acting Commander of the agency in the state, Mr. Isaac Aloye, disclosed this to newsmen in Minna on Thursday that the com­mand also secured the con­viction of 28 suspects at the Federal High Court Minna to different jail terms for being in possession of and trafficking in drugs. He said that drugs seized from the suspects include 3,066.9334 kg of cannabis sa­tiva (Indian hemp), 0.014 kg of cocaine, 0.001 kg of meth­amphetamine and 62.05kg of psychotropic substances. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “The command also se­cured the final forfeiture of 10 vehicles used from convict­ed drug dealers and tempo­rary forfeiture of 20 others. “This is a great feat in the history of the com­mand and a great disin­centive to drug dealers and would-be dealers alike that drug doesn’t pay,’’ the com­mander said. Anambra: One Dead, Four Injured In Multiple Motor Accidents Nursing Mother, Three Others Crushed In Delta Auto Crashes Aloye said that the quan­tity and quality of the var­ious drugs seized during the period of COVID-19 lockdown in the state was of great concern as most of them were transported as waybill goods. “The agency is worried that drug traffickers now waybill the drugs to physical­ly distance themselves from the drugs upon interception. “It takes a great deal to trace and arrest the recip­ients and senders of the drugs,’’ he said. The commander said that the agency would not relent in frustrating the activities of drug peddlers in the state and the nation at large. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION